<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse regioonide komitee arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 189b of the Treaty (4) in the light of the joint text approved by the Conciliation Committee on 16 April 1997, </inglise>
<eesti> toimides asutamislepingu artiklis 189b s&auml;testatud korras (4) vastavalt lepituskomitees 16. aprillil 1997 heakskiidetud &uuml;histekstile, </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Whereas, pursuant to Article 3 (o) of the Treaty, Community action must include a contribution towards the attainment of a high level of health protection; whereas Article 129 of the Treaty expressly provides for Community competence in this field in so far as the Community contributes to it by encouraging cooperation between the Member States and, if necessary, by lending support to their action; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1) vastavalt asutamislepingu artikli 3 l&otilde;ikele o peab &uuml;henduse tegevus sisaldama panust tervisekaitse k&otilde;rge taseme saavutamisse; asutamislepingu artiklis 129 s&auml;testatakse &uuml;henduse p&auml;devus selles valdkonnas, kuiv&otilde;rd &uuml;hendus annab sellesse oma panuse, ergutades liikmesriikidevahelist koost&ouml;&ouml;d ja vajaduse korral toetades nende tegevust; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Whereas the Council, in its resolution of 27 May 1993 on future action in the field of public health (5), considered that improved collection, analysis and distribution of health data, as well as an improvement in the quality and comparability of available data, are essential for the preparation of future programmes; </inglise>
<eesti> 2) n&otilde;ukogu arvas oma 27. mai 1993. aasta resolutsioonis tulevase tegevuse kohta rahvatervise valdkonnas, (5) et tervishoiuandmete paranenud kogumine, anal&uuml;&uuml;simine ja levitamine ning k&auml;ttesaadavate andmete kvaliteedi ja v&otilde;rreldavuse parandamine on tulevaste programmide ettevalmistamise seisukohalt oluline; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Whereas the European Parliament, in its resolution on public health policy after Maastricht (6), stressed the importance of having sufficient and relevant information as a basis for the development of Community actions in the field of public health; whereas the European Parliament called on the Commission to collect and examine health data from Member States with a view to analysing the effects of public health policies on health status in the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> 3) Euroopa Parlament r&otilde;hutas oma resolutsioonis tervishoiupoliitika kohta p&auml;rast Maastrichti (6), kui oluline on piisava ja asjakohase teabe olemasolu &uuml;henduse tegevuse arendamiseks rahvatervise valdkonnas; Euroopa Parlament kutsus komisjoni &uuml;les koguma ja l&auml;bi vaatama liikmesriikide tervishoiuandmeid, et anal&uuml;&uuml;sida tervishoiupoliitika m&otilde;ju tervislikule seisundile &uuml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) Whereas it would be desirable to study the feasibility of establishing a permanent structure for the monitoring and evaluation of European Community health data and indicators; </inglise>
<eesti> 4) on soovitav uurida, kas oleks v&otilde;imalik asutada p&uuml;sistruktuur Euroopa &Uuml;henduse tervishoiuandmete ja -n&auml;itajate j&auml;lgimiseks ja hindamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) Whereas the Commission, in its communication of 24 November 1993 on the framework for action in the field of public health, regarded increased cooperation on standardization and collection of comparable/compatible data on health, and the promotion of systems of health monitoring and surveillance as a prerequisite for the establishment of a framework for supporting Member States' policies and programmes; whereas the area of health monitoring, including health data and indicators, has been identified as a priority area for proposals on multiannual Community programmes in the field of public health; </inglise>
<eesti> 5) komisjon leidis oma 24. novembri 1993. aasta teatises tegevusraamistiku kohta rahvatervise valdkonnas, et suurenenud koost&ouml;&ouml; v&otilde;rreldavate/kokkusobivate tervishoiuandmete standardimisel ja kogumisel ning terviseseire ja -kontrolli edendamine on liikmesriikide poliitikat ja programme toetava raamistiku sisseseadmise eeltingimuseks; terviseseire, sealhulgas tervishoiuandmed ja -n&auml;itajad on eelisvaldkonnaks ettepanekute tegemisel &uuml;henduse mitmeaastaste rahvatervise programmide kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) Whereas in its resolution of 2 June 1994 on the framework for action in the field of Community health (7), the Council indicated that the collection of health data should be accorded priority and invited the Commission to present relevant proposals; whereas the Council considered that data and indicators used should include measures relating to the quality of life of the population, accurate assessments of health needs, estimates of the avoidable deaths from the prevention of diseases, socio-economic factors in health among different population groups, and, where appropriate and if the Member States judge it necessary, health aid, medical practices, and the impact of reforms; </inglise>
<eesti> 6) n&otilde;ukogu n&auml;itas oma 2. juuni 1994. aasta resolutsioonis tegevusraamistiku kohta &uuml;henduse rahvatervise valdkonnas, (7) et tervishoiuandmete kogumine tuleks seada esikohale, ja kutsus komisjoni &uuml;les esitama asjakohaseid ettepanekuid; n&otilde;ukogu arvas, et kasutatud andmed ja n&auml;itajad peaksid sisaldama elanikkonna elukvaliteediga seotud meetmeid, tervisega seotud vajaduste t&auml;pset hindamist, hinnangut haiguste ennetamisega v&auml;lditavate surmajuhtumite arvu kohta, eri rahvastikur&uuml;hmade tervist m&otilde;jutavaid sotsiaal-majanduslikke tegureid ja vajaduse korral, kui liikmesriigid peavad seda vajalikuks, tervisehooldust, meditsiinitavasid ja uuenduste m&otilde;ju; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) Whereas health monitoring at Community level is essential for the planning, monitoring and assessment of Community actions in the field of public health, and the monitoring and assessment of the health impact of other Community policies; </inglise>
<eesti> 7) terviseseire &uuml;henduse tasandil on oluline &uuml;henduse tegevuse planeerimiseks, j&auml;relevalveks ja hindamiseks rahvatervise valdkonnas ning selleks, et j&auml;lgida ja hinnata muu &uuml;henduse poliitika m&otilde;ju tervishoiule; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) Whereas, on the basis in particular of knowledge of data relating to public health in Europe obtained by setting up a Community health monitoring system, it will be possible to monitor public health trends and define public health priorities and objectives; </inglise>
<eesti> 8) eelk&otilde;ige nende teadmiste alusel, mis on seotud Euroopa rahvatervise andmetega ja mis on saadud &uuml;henduse terviseseires&uuml;steemi kehtestamisega, on v&otilde;imalik j&auml;lgida rahvatervise suundumusi ning m&auml;&auml;ratleda rahvatervise prioriteedid ja eesm&auml;rgid; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Whereas health monitoring, for the purposes of this Decision, encompasses the establishment of Community health indicators and the collection, dissemination and analysis of Community health data and indicators; </inglise>
